(12, 'MSB/CB/B-159(A)', 'Govt servant involved into business', 'Parawise Comment on WP (C) 5958/2009 Team Life Core Insurance (India Pvt. Ltd.-VS-Union of India & ORS', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.0pt\">OFFICE OF THE SUPERINTENDENT OF POLICE</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16.0pt\">CID (SB)&nbsp; :&nbsp;&nbsp; MIZORAM&nbsp; :&nbsp; AIZAWL</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">No. MSB/CB/B-159-A/09/&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Dated Aizawl the 5th March, 2010</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">To</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">The Director General of Police</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Mizoram, Aizawl</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Subject&nbsp;&nbsp; : &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Parawise Comment on WP (C) 5958/2009 Team Life Core Insurance (India Pvt. Ltd.-VS-Union of India &amp; ORS</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Ref.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No. LC/PHQ/144/2010/64 Dt. 2.3.2010</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Sir,</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Please refer to your letter No. cited above, in pursuance of the letter parawise comment on the above writ petition is submitted for further necessary action.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>1. PARAWISE COMMENT</strong>:- On the Writ Petition (C) No.-5958/09 in c/w Misc Case No. 66/2010 submitted by Team Life Care Insurance (India) Pvt. Ltd., TLC Building, Sh. Ayyappe Arcade, 4-A, Pampa Enter, Hebbal, Kempapura, Bangalore-560024, Andhra Pradesh to the Guwahati High Court.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>2. SI No. 5 Para-I</strong> &ndash; Manipur Police to comment</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>3. PARA 5(II):</strong> The Mizoram Police CID (SB) had not freeze any account of the petitioner nor had interfered with the conduct of seminar or promotional meetings held for the co-ordinators and prospective co-ordinators.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">In addition to the above mentioned fact, the said para 5 (II) mentioned that local police interfered with seminar/promotional meeting conducted by the petitioner on 13.12.09 at &ldquo;Conference Hall&rdquo;, Babutlang, Aizawl-796001. Enquiry revealed that there is no building or hall designated as &ldquo;Conference Hall&rdquo; at the locality mentioned i.e. Babutlang. The following four centres are located at Babutlang which could possibly be used for such seminars, which are as follows:-</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Archive Hall</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Engineers Club</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">YMA Conference Hall</span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Co-operative Conference Hall </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Contacting the authorities of the above said 4 halls revealed that none of them had been hired on the date cited in the Writ Petition i.e. 13.12.09 not to mention the alleged interference by the Police. Further mentioned be made that business seminar/promotional meeting are hardly conducted on Sundays if not at all, which was the day on which 13.12.09 falls, as Mizoram is a Christian State. Therefore, the question arising is whether the claimed seminar was in fact really conducted by the petitioner or not, rather than the allegation that Mizoram Police interfere with it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>4. SI No. 5 Para-III &ndash; </strong>Nagaland Police to comment</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>5. SI No. 5 Para-IV &ndash; </strong>Assam Police to comment</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Superintendent of Police</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">CID (SB), Mizoram, Aizawl</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '23/10/2007', '2007-10-23', '<p>MSB/CB/B-159(A)</p> <p>Govt servant involved into business</p> <p>Parawise Comment on WP (C) 5958/2009 Team Life Core Insurance (India Pvt. Ltd.-VS-Union of India & ORS</p> <p><p style=\"text-align:left\">OFFICE OF THE SUPERINTENDENT OF POLICE</p> <p style=\"text-align:left\">CID (SB) : MIZORAM : AIZAWL</p>  <p>No. MSB/CB/B-159-A/09/                                                                              Dated Aizawl the 5th March, 2010</p>  <p>To</p>  <p style=\"margin-left:48px\">The Director General of Police</p> <p style=\"margin-left:48px\">Mizoram, Aizawl</p>  <p>Subject :  Parawise Comment on WP (C) 5958/2009 Team Life Core Insurance (India Pvt. Ltd.-VS-Union of India &amp; ORS</p>  <p>Ref. :  No. LC/PHQ/144/2010/64 Dt. 2.3.2010</p>  <p>Sir,</p>  <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Please refer to your letter No. cited above, in pursuance of the letter parawise comment on the above writ petition is submitted for further necessary action.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">1. PARAWISE COMMENT:- On the Writ Petition (C) No.-5958/09 in c/w Misc Case No. 66/2010 submitted by Team Life Care Insurance (India) Pvt. Ltd., TLC Building, Sh. Ayyappe Arcade, 4-A, Pampa Enter, Hebbal, Kempapura, Bangalore-560024, Andhra Pradesh to the Guwahati High Court.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">2. SI No. 5 Para-I  Manipur Police to comment</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">3. PARA 5(II): The Mizoram Police CID (SB) had not freeze any account of the petitioner nor had interfered with the conduct of seminar or promotional meetings held for the co-ordinators and prospective co-ordinators.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition to the above mentioned fact, the said para 5 (II) mentioned that local police interfered with seminar/promotional meeting conducted by the petitioner on 13.12.09 at &ldquo;Conference Hall&rdquo;, Babutlang, Aizawl-796001. Enquiry revealed that there is no building or hall designated as &ldquo;Conference Hall&rdquo; at the locality mentioned i.e. Babutlang. The following four centres are located at Babutlang which could possibly be used for such seminars, which are as follows:-</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> Archive Hall Engineers Club YMA Conference Hall Co-operative Conference Hall <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Contacting the authorities of the above said 4 halls revealed that none of them had been hired on the date cited in the Writ Petition i.e. 13.12.09 not to mention the alleged interference by the Police. Further mentioned be made that business seminar/promotional meeting are hardly conducted on Sundays if not at all, which was the day on which 13.12.09 falls, as Mizoram is a Christian State. Therefore, the question arising is whether the claimed seminar was in fact really conducted by the petitioner or not, rather than the allegation that Mizoram Police interfere with it.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">4. SI No. 5 Para-III  Nagaland Police to comment</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">5. SI No. 5 Para-IV  Assam Police to comment</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:left\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:left\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:left\">Superintendent of Police</p> <p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:left\">CID (SB), Mizoram, Aizawl</p> <p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:left\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:left\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:360px; text-align:left\"></p> </p>'),
(13, 'MSB/CB/A-7', 'Enquiry against Police Officers & men', 'PROCEEDING OF PRELIMINARY HEARING IN RESPECT OF Inspr. TIALTHAWNGA (u/s) OF 3rd Bn. MAP', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt\">PROCEEDING OF PRELIMINARY HEARING IN RESPECT OF </span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt\">Inspr. TIALTHAWNGA (u/s) OF 3rd Bn. MAP</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">(CHARGED OFFICER)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Q1. Did you receive the charge memorandum and its connected documents?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Charged Officer</strong>:- Yes, I received it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Q2. Did you admit all the 3 charges (Article of charges) framed against you?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Charged Officer</strong>: - I fully admit Article of charge No. 3. But I flatly denied articles of charge No. I and II</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Q3. Did you receive the appointment order of Enquiry Officer?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Charged Officer</strong>: - Yes</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Q4. Did you accept the appointment of Pu K. Lalremsanga as Enquiry Officer to enquire into the charges framed against you?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Charged Officer</strong>: - I accept the appointment of Pu K. Lalremsanga as Enquiry Officer.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Q5. Do you want to engage Defence Assistant?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Charged Officer</strong>: - Yes, I want to engage Defence Assistance.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Q6. Name your proposal for Defence Assistant?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Charged Officer</strong>: - Pu C. Vanramlawma, Dy. SP (Rtd.), Dinthar Veng, Aizawl.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Q7. Do you want to engage Defence Witness?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Charged Officer</strong>: - Yes, I want to call Inspr. Raldokima of 1st Bn. MAP as my defence witness.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">Q8. Do you have any supporting document to submit?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>Charged Officer</strong>: - I have no documents to submit at the moment. I may have it later.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; RO &amp; AC&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Recorded by,</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">(<strong>Inspr. TIALTHAWNGA</strong>) u/s&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (<strong>K. LALREMSANGA</strong>)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Charged Officer&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Addl. SP, CID (SB)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enquiry Officer</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '15/07/2009', '2009-07-15', '<p>MSB/CB/A-7</p> <p>Enquiry against Police Officers & men</p> <p>PROCEEDING OF PRELIMINARY HEARING IN RESPECT OF Inspr. TIALTHAWNGA (u/s) OF 3rd Bn. MAP</p> <p><p style=\"text-align:left\">PROCEEDING OF PRELIMINARY HEARING IN RESPECT OF </p> <p style=\"text-align:left\">Inspr. TIALTHAWNGA (u/s) OF 3rd Bn. MAP</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">(CHARGED OFFICER)</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q1. Did you receive the charge memorandum and its connected documents?</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Charged Officer:- Yes, I received it.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q2. Did you admit all the 3 charges (Article of charges) framed against you?</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Charged Officer: - I fully admit Article of charge No. 3. But I flatly denied articles of charge No. I and II</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q3. Did you receive the appointment order of Enquiry Officer?</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Charged Officer: - Yes</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q4. Did you accept the appointment of Pu K. Lalremsanga as Enquiry Officer to enquire into the charges framed against you?</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Charged Officer: - I accept the appointment of Pu K. Lalremsanga as Enquiry Officer.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q5. Do you want to engage Defence Assistant?</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Charged Officer: - Yes, I want to engage Defence Assistance.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q6. Name your proposal for Defence Assistant?</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Charged Officer: - Pu C. Vanramlawma, Dy. SP (Rtd.), Dinthar Veng, Aizawl.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q7. Do you want to engage Defence Witness?</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Charged Officer: - Yes, I want to call Inspr. Raldokima of 1st Bn. MAP as my defence witness.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Q8. Do you have any supporting document to submit?</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Charged Officer: - I have no documents to submit at the moment. I may have it later.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"> RO &amp; AC   Recorded by,</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">(Inspr. TIALTHAWNGA) u/s (K. LALREMSANGA)</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"> Charged Officer  Addl. SP, CID (SB)</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">  Enquiry Officer</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p></p>'),
(14, 'MSB/CB/C-118', 'CADC(Chakma Autonomous District Council)', 'Reproduction of Enquiry Report', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">To</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The Superintendent of Police</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">CID (SB), Mizoram, Aizawl</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Subject &nbsp;&nbsp;: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reproduction of Enquiry Report</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Sir,</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">I am to state that enquiry into the suspicious transaction into the private bank account of Pu Sushil Jiban Chakma, employee of CADC, Kamalanagar, Lawngtlai District, Mizoram was conducted by Inspr. HT Sapsanga, SO, CID (SB), Lawngtlai whose report is translated and reproduced in English and am herby submitting it for your kind perusal and further necessary action.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">&ldquo;In response to your order, I have enquired about the suspicious transaction of Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma, CADC, Kamalanagar, Lawngtlai District, Mizoram who worked as cashier with a private Bank Account No. 00000011695402797 other than the previous report which I submitted earlier (12.10.09). The current document is enclosed.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">My enquiry findings of Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma (Ex-Cashier), who is now an Assistant at CADC&rsquo;s, Private Bank Account (Suspicious Transaction) are as follows:-</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">1. &nbsp; On 2nd June, 2009 Mrs. KT Thangi of Electric Veng, Aizawl who worked on the project of Parva-I to Simenasora Road (Upgradation of Parva-I to Simenasora Road under Non-Lapsable Central Pool of Resource) requested Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma to transfer their bill drawn from State Bank of India, Lawngtlai Branch to their account No. 0010763505283 which Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma transferred from his Private Bank Account No. 00000011695402797.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">I have also enclosed the (1) Work Order (2) Progress Report for Quarter ending September, 2009 and (3) Rs. 233.22 Lakhs of KT Thangi and the authority letter from Executive Secretary, CADC, Kamalanagar.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The cash (Rs. 233.22 lakhs) which the Financial Intelligence Unit-India (FIU-IND) Ministry of Finance, suspects does not belong to Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma, it is the property of the contractor, KT Thangi.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">2. &nbsp; With the permission of the executive secretary, PB Chakma (who does not hold this position at present), Rs. 1.48 lakhs was drawn from Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Private Account on 5th February, 2009 which is said to have been disbursed. For this withdrawal, Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma stated that the executive secretary signed in the cheque No. 329801 (CADC).</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><em><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Cont&hellip;&hellip;.next</span></em></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">3. &nbsp; In 1st July, 2008, a cash of Rs. 2.21 lakhs (HUDCO loan of CADC) was drawn and transferred from Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Private Account with the permission of CADC&rsquo;s Executive Secretary, PB Chakma. It is evident that they repay the loan. I have also enclosed the repayment draft of the loan from the Regional Chief, HUDCO, Regional Office, Old Secretariat Complex, Kohima 797001 (Nagaland) which is Rs. 2.21 lakhs, which is in the transaction of Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Private Account. It seems like the money does not belong to him.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">4. &nbsp; Financial Intelligence Unit-India (FIU-IND) Ministry of Finance notify that on 30th April, 2009 there was a transfer debit of Rs. 12.03 lakhs on Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Private Account No. 00000011695402797 this appears to be a mistake mad by the FIU-IND because from my previous enquiry, State Bank of India, Lawngtlai Branch, Sushil Jiban Chakma, Bank statement of account w.e.f. 28.04.08 to 30.06.09, draw/transfer Rs. 12.03 lakhs from his account on 30.4.2008 (not on 30.4.2009). This cash is nor a private cash of Sushil Jiban Chakma but the cash of CADC (HUDCO loan). This cash is said to have been used to repay the HUDCO loan.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">My enquiry reveals that the CADC leaders (Executive secretary), let their cashier use their Personal Bank Account for their convenience in dealing with the Bank.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">At the time when Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma opened his account, he was merely a government employee as cashier, but the transaction on his Bank Account shows &lsquo;high value transaction&rsquo;. For this reason, it seems that the Financial Intelligence Unit-India (FIU-IND), Ministry of Finance were suspicious of him.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The revelation of my enquiry of the transaction of Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Bank Account which FIU-IND suspected&nbsp; are written above&rdquo;.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">I therefore submitted herewith enclosed copy in order to take further investigation and necessary action.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Yours faithfully,</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">(<strong>LALRINAWMA</strong>) MPS</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Addl. Superintendent of Police</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">CID (SB), Mizoram, Aizawl</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '23/10/2007', '2007-10-23', '<p>MSB/CB/C-118</p> <p>CADC(Chakma Autonomous District Council)</p> <p>Reproduction of Enquiry Report</p> <p><p style=\"text-align:justify\">To</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\">The Superintendent of Police</p> <p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:justify\">CID (SB), Mizoram, Aizawl</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Subject :  Reproduction of Enquiry Report</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">Sir,</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">I am to state that enquiry into the suspicious transaction into the private bank account of Pu Sushil Jiban Chakma, employee of CADC, Kamalanagar, Lawngtlai District, Mizoram was conducted by Inspr. HT Sapsanga, SO, CID (SB), Lawngtlai whose report is translated and reproduced in English and am herby submitting it for your kind perusal and further necessary action.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">&ldquo;In response to your order, I have enquired about the suspicious transaction of Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma, CADC, Kamalanagar, Lawngtlai District, Mizoram who worked as cashier with a private Bank Account No. 00000011695402797 other than the previous report which I submitted earlier (12.10.09). The current document is enclosed.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">My enquiry findings of Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma (Ex-Cashier), who is now an Assistant at CADC&rsquo;s, Private Bank Account (Suspicious Transaction) are as follows:-</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">1.  On 2nd June, 2009 Mrs. KT Thangi of Electric Veng, Aizawl who worked on the project of Parva-I to Simenasora Road (Upgradation of Parva-I to Simenasora Road under Non-Lapsable Central Pool of Resource) requested Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma to transfer their bill drawn from State Bank of India, Lawngtlai Branch to their account No. 0010763505283 which Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma transferred from his Private Bank Account No. 00000011695402797.</p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">I have also enclosed the (1) Work Order (2) Progress Report for Quarter ending September, 2009 and (3) Rs. 233.22 Lakhs of KT Thangi and the authority letter from Executive Secretary, CADC, Kamalanagar.</p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">The cash (Rs. 233.22 lakhs) which the Financial Intelligence Unit-India (FIU-IND) Ministry of Finance, suspects does not belong to Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma, it is the property of the contractor, KT Thangi.</p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">2.  With the permission of the executive secretary, PB Chakma (who does not hold this position at present), Rs. 1.48 lakhs was drawn from Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Private Account on 5th February, 2009 which is said to have been disbursed. For this withdrawal, Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma stated that the executive secretary signed in the cheque No. 329801 (CADC).</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:right\">Cont&hellip;&hellip;.next</p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">3.  In 1st July, 2008, a cash of Rs. 2.21 lakhs (HUDCO loan of CADC) was drawn and transferred from Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Private Account with the permission of CADC&rsquo;s Executive Secretary, PB Chakma. It is evident that they repay the loan. I have also enclosed the repayment draft of the loan from the Regional Chief, HUDCO, Regional Office, Old Secretariat Complex, Kohima 797001 (Nagaland) which is Rs. 2.21 lakhs, which is in the transaction of Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Private Account. It seems like the money does not belong to him.</p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:24px; text-align:justify\">4.  Financial Intelligence Unit-India (FIU-IND) Ministry of Finance notify that on 30th April, 2009 there was a transfer debit of Rs. 12.03 lakhs on Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Private Account No. 00000011695402797 this appears to be a mistake mad by the FIU-IND because from my previous enquiry, State Bank of India, Lawngtlai Branch, Sushil Jiban Chakma, Bank statement of account w.e.f. 28.04.08 to 30.06.09, draw/transfer Rs. 12.03 lakhs from his account on 30.4.2008 (not on 30.4.2009). This cash is nor a private cash of Sushil Jiban Chakma but the cash of CADC (HUDCO loan). This cash is said to have been used to repay the HUDCO loan.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">My enquiry reveals that the CADC leaders (Executive secretary), let their cashier use their Personal Bank Account for their convenience in dealing with the Bank.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">At the time when Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma opened his account, he was merely a government employee as cashier, but the transaction on his Bank Account shows &lsquo;high value transaction&rsquo;. For this reason, it seems that the Financial Intelligence Unit-India (FIU-IND), Ministry of Finance were suspicious of him.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">The revelation of my enquiry of the transaction of Mr. Sushil Jiban Chakma&rsquo;s Bank Account which FIU-IND suspected are written above&rdquo;.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\">I therefore submitted herewith enclosed copy in order to take further investigation and necessary action.</p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"text-align:justify\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\">Yours faithfully,</p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\"></p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\">(LALRINAWMA) MPS</p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\">Addl. Superintendent of Police</p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\">CID (SB), Mizoram, Aizawl</p> <p style=\"margin-left:384px; text-align:left\"></p></p>'),
(15, 'MSB/CB/B-61/Misc', 'Miscellaneous', 'SERLUI-B HRAI CHUNGCHANG', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>SERLUI-B HRAI CHUNGCHANG&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I. Kolasib PS C/No. 92/09 Dt. 23.11.09 u/s 284/428 IPC&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accused - Unknown<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Heng mite hi Police Station-ah thu zawhfiah ani a, an inhnamhnawihna hi prove a ni lo.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1. Lalbiakliana (40) s/o Kapthuama (L), N. Hlimen<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;2. Lalvenhima (32) s/o Lalhmuchhuaka, N. Hlimen<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;3. Lalrammawia (23) s/o Thandanga, N. Hlimen<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;4. RC Lalhmachhuana s/o RC Lalsanglura, N. Hlimen</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Hemi tum hian tura hrai ni lovin Bomb hman a ni. Case hi la kalmek ani in tumah inhnamhnawih hriat ani lo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>II. Vairengte PS C/ No. 70/09 Dt. 22.11.09 u/s 428 IPC r/w 43 Water Prevention &amp; Control of Pollution Act 1974.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accused - Unknown<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Heng mite hi thu zawhfiah anni a, mahse an involved na prove ani lo.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1. Jessie Lalremtluanga s/o Lalngheta, N. Chawnpui<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;2. Laldinpuia s/o kamdingliana, N. Chawnpui</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;A Sangha thi FSL-ah examine tura thawn ani a, FSL hian tur an hmu lo tih report dawn ani a. An examination result pakhat zawk la nghah mek avangin case hi pending a ni.Tur a hrai ani tih hi tunthleng chuan prove theih ani lo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>III. Kawnpui PS C/No. 9/2010 Dt. 12.3.2010 u/s 284 IPC r/w 43 of Water Prevention and Control of Pollution Act 1974</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A hnuaia mite hi accused an niin man an ni.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1. Lalawmpuia s/o Lalringngheta, Durtlang Leitan<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;2. Lalbiaktluanga s/o Lalremthanga,Durtlang Leitan<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;3. K. Lalnuntluanga s./o K. Malsawma,Durtlang Leitan<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;4. Lalfakzuala s/o Lalrozama,Durtlang Leitan<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;5. Vanlalhruaia s/o Thanzinga,Durtlang Leitan<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;6. K. Lalremsanga s/o K. Laldingliana,Durtlang Leitan<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;7. Lalhmachhuana s/o Lalmawia,Durtlang Leitan<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;8. K. Pahlira s/o K. Dengdaia,Durtlang Leitan<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;9. Thanchungnunga s/o Vanchhunga, Kawnpui Hmar Veng</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ni 12.3.10 vek hian chargesheet (CS No. 6/10 Dt. 12.3.10) &nbsp;an ni a. Court -in bail in a chhuah leh tawh a ni.Tur a hrai ani tih prove chiah ani lova, Chinai an hmang ni a rin a ni.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '23/10/2007', '2007-10-23', '<p>MSB/CB/B-61/Misc</p> <p>Miscellaneous</p> <p>SERLUI-B HRAI CHUNGCHANG</p> <p><p style=\"text-align:left\">SERLUI-B HRAI CHUNGCHANG</p> <p>I. Kolasib PS C/No. 92/09 Dt. 23.11.09 u/s 284/428 IPC</p> <p> Accused - Unknown  Heng mite hi Police Station-ah thu zawhfiah ani a, an inhnamhnawihna hi prove a ni lo.  1. Lalbiakliana (40) s/o Kapthuama (L), N. Hlimen  2. Lalvenhima (32) s/o Lalhmuchhuaka, N. Hlimen  3. Lalrammawia (23) s/o Thandanga, N. Hlimen  4. RC Lalhmachhuana s/o RC Lalsanglura, N. Hlimen</p> <p> Hemi tum hian tura hrai ni lovin Bomb hman a ni. Case hi la kalmek ani in tumah inhnamhnawih hriat ani lo.</p> <p>II. Vairengte PS C/ No. 70/09 Dt. 22.11.09 u/s 428 IPC r/w 43 Water Prevention &amp; Control of Pollution Act 1974.</p> <p> Accused - Unknown  Heng mite hi thu zawhfiah anni a, mahse an involved na prove ani lo.  1. Jessie Lalremtluanga s/o Lalngheta, N. Chawnpui  2. Laldinpuia s/o kamdingliana, N. Chawnpui</p> <p> A Sangha thi FSL-ah examine tura thawn ani a, FSL hian tur an hmu lo tih report dawn ani a. An examination result pakhat zawk la nghah mek avangin case hi pending a ni.Tur a hrai ani tih hi tunthleng chuan prove theih ani lo.</p> <p>III. Kawnpui PS C/No. 9/2010 Dt. 12.3.2010 u/s 284 IPC r/w 43 of Water Prevention and Control of Pollution Act 1974</p> <p>A hnuaia mite hi accused an niin man an ni.</p> <p> 1. Lalawmpuia s/o Lalringngheta, Durtlang Leitan  2. Lalbiaktluanga s/o Lalremthanga,Durtlang Leitan  3. K. Lalnuntluanga s./o K. Malsawma,Durtlang Leitan  4. Lalfakzuala s/o Lalrozama,Durtlang Leitan  5. Vanlalhruaia s/o Thanzinga,Durtlang Leitan  6. K. Lalremsanga s/o K. Laldingliana,Durtlang Leitan  7. Lalhmachhuana s/o Lalmawia,Durtlang Leitan  8. K. Pahlira s/o K. Dengdaia,Durtlang Leitan  9. Thanchungnunga s/o Vanchhunga, Kawnpui Hmar Veng</p> <p>Ni 12.3.10 vek hian chargesheet (CS No. 6/10 Dt. 12.3.10) an ni a. Court -in bail in a chhuah leh tawh a ni.Tur a hrai ani tih prove chiah ani lova, Chinai an hmang ni a rin a ni.</p></p>');
