(29, 'MSB/CB/B-167', 'Bru Revolutionary Army (BRU)/BRA/BRAM', 'PRESS NOTE On 13.11.2009 @ 10:00 am Zarzokima (18)', '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong><u>PRESS NOTE</u></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; On 13.11.2009 @ 10:00 am Zarzokima (18) s/0 Lalngilneia of Bungthuam was shot dead @ 1 km north of Bungthuam village by unidentified persons. The culprit left a note in which they claimed themselves as Bru Revolutionary Union (BRU) and that they did not want their repatriation without proper agreement and would fight the State Government for their rights. In this connection, Kanhmun Police Station case No. 23/09 Dt. 13.11.09 u/s 302 IPC r/w 25(1B)(a)/27(1) Arms Act had been registered and investigation is going on.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Superintendent of Police, Mamit District, SDPO Kawrthah and OC Kanhmun immediately rushed to the place of occurrence and camping there till date. The State Government also directed all the nearby BOPs and Police Stations for prompt action in tracing out the miscreants.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; While efforts were being made to solve the case by Police, Mizo Community around Bungthuam village made announcement of their willingness to apprehend the culprits themselves. In the process some extremist set ablaze houses villages as shown below.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbs